<p>Recycling of human meat: Since people seem to be addicted to eating meat, it seems we could potentially alleviate the hunger problem in the future by recycling dead humans as food. This is definitely less popular, but as someone who has worked as a mortuary, I can tell you that a great deal of viable food goes to waste. Seeing that animals consume such a great deal of resources, it seems foolish not to take advantage of food that raises itself. Not to say that humans should be viewed as food, but there's always potential.</p>
